Fields.DialogueText: *ALARM*
@BATTLE
It's easier to hear you if you stop running away, you know.
BWOO-ska-VEE-tsah.

Fields.MenuText: She doesn't know what you said.
Could you repeat it again for her?
It's exactly what you said.

Fields.DialogueText: It was just how to pronounce my name.
Blyskawica. That is my name.
Either your ears are mistaken or your tongue is.
Boots of Whiskey?
I think that is not what I said.
Why are you so slow, Kapitan?
I'm literally *huff* sprinting!
I cannot believe you are sprinting slower than I was walking!
I wouldn't call what you were doing "walking."
Well, then you should--
And you went through several bulkheads, which forced me to take alternate routes.
Did I? Oh, well.
So what was the question you were asking?
A lot of the international crew were wondering how to pronounce your name. I was wondering if-
How is she already gone again?
Moving! Good talk!
Why are you making significant headway away from people when you speak to them?
Captain, help me out here?
At least you're quick on the draw...
Anyway, I wanted to--
By the way, there is a Morgana approaching.
Kapitan! I had an idea!
And what exactly is this idea?
Captain, here are your dail--
What if we have a competition?
Did she just ask you something and run away?
She'll be back...
Kapitan! We should do an athletic competition!

Fields.MenuText: What kind of athletic competition?

Fields.DialogueText: @BATTLE
*ALARM*

Fields.MenuText: Welcome back. How was your run around the deck?
That sounds fun!

Fields.DialogueText: I have no idea yet, but I am sure it will be grand!
I think it is easier when we are being shot at. It also gave me time to think about my competition!
It certainly does! I'm so excited!
Do you already have a plan to set up this competition?
No! I do not have any ideas yet!
And she's gone again. Does she ever stop?
Honestly? I'm not sure if she is capable of slowing down, much less stopping.
Anyway, your daily reports...
... At some point.
Oh, Kapitan! I am so excited!
So what exactly brought about this idea of an "athletic competition?"
*ALARM*
@BATTLE
Well, I was running, and I thought I wanted to see how fast the other Corki Juracie were compared to me! On foot, of course.
I know what our engines can do, but I can train this body! Maybe they've been practicing too! Oh, I bet I can outrun them!
Blyskawica...
Oh! Maybe I can jump better too!
Wait, should the contest be for jumping farther or higher?
Blyskawica! THERE ARE MORGANAS APPROACHING!
Huh? Oh! Why didn't you say so earlier, Kapitan? We could have caught them by surprise! Well, no matter. What are your orders?
So as I was saying--
You were telling me why you got the idea for the competition.
Oh, yes! When I was running I thought it would be nice if other girls would join me for my daily exercise.
Then I wondered if I was faster than them, and then I thought that the answer might change if it was just these new bodies instead of our actual engines!

Fields.MenuText: You've said this part already.
Don't get carried away.
And that's when you brought it to me?

Fields.DialogueText: Did I? Oh yes, I did! But without the daily exercise part. I think that's important. I really think it would do some of these girls a lot of good to--
I won't get carried away.  I just wanted to know if you think a running jump or standing long jump is a better--
I actually did three more laps around the hull before I brought it to you. Then we fought the Morganas, and then we--
Focus, Blyskawica.
Oh no, I distracted myself again!  So, Kapitan, what do you think?
It's a good idea, actually.  But what kind of events did you want to have?
Still working on it. Another few laps should help narrow it down...
Kapitan, I was thinking about what you said, and I started thinking about more things, so I started running. You know I do my best thinking while running.
... Wow. I don't think I've ever seen you sitting at a desk before.  What are you doing?
So I thought of so many different ideas for contests, and then I didn't write any of them down!
Well it's good that you have ideas. What did you come up with?
That is the problem! I do not remember what I thought of after the ten-meter handstand-dash!

Fields.MenuText: The what?
Did you just say "handstand-dash?"
How about the twenty-meter handstand-dash?

Fields.DialogueText: I have tried, and I can only make it fifteen meters at high speed.  I'm getting better!
Yes! I think it will be a very fun event!
The ten-meter handstand-dash.  You stand on your hands and try to go ten meters as quickly as you can.
Kapitan, Kapitan!
@BATTLE
Here, I'll show you!
*HANDSTEPS*
I kind of feel sorry for whichever crew member was on the other side of that bulkhead. She probably just scared the daylights out of somebody.
*THUD*
Welcome back, Blyskawica.  Is everyone all right on the other side?
Tak, but I saw Morganas approaching when I was outside!  I wonder if I can last the entire fight upside down?
Yes! It has made a wonderful dance floor.
And I see you have all the Polish sailors... dancing?
*FOOTSTEPS*
I see you've moved every single table in the mess hall.
They have been trying. Their efforts are good, but they are slow.

Fields.MenuText: I don't think they're that slow.
Perhaps you're faster than you think.
It looks like some of them are getting the hang of it.

Fields.DialogueText: Are you sure? They cannot keep up with me.
Really? Oh, I really hope so, Kapitan!
Yes! And it has only been an hour!
What kind of a dance is it, anyway?
It is the Oberek. It is a dance of lovers! Very romantic, I think.
Well, really, it is just a dance involving a lot of spinning.
And jumping, and holding...
*THUD*
Cholera! He also could not keep up with me.
Lieutenant?
Captain?
Get those tired sailors to the doc and--
*ALARM*
The rest of you have a battle to fight!
@BATTLE

Fields.Title: Conversation 5
Fields.Description: Blyskawica tries to teach some of the crew the Oberek

Fields.DialogueText: No, Kapitan. I was busy.
Some of the sailors have been complaining that you've been shocking them.
Finally caught you. Did you notice you were running away from me?
I already promised to stop going through bulkheads... so often.
No, literally shocking them.
Oh! The ones that yelp like children while I am on my run!

Fields.MenuText: Now, I don't think that's very nice.
Yes, those ones.
Do they really yelp like that?

Fields.DialogueText: O nie! It is just how I remembered who you mean.  I am very sorry!
O nie! Where are they?  I will apologize!
Some of them very loudly. O nie - I must be hurting them!
Just be sure to apologize if you hear them... uh, yelping.
Kapitan, I sense Morganas approaching!
YAIP!
Przepraszam!
@BATTLE
Kapitan, Kapitan!
Writing while walking like that seems difficult.
It is very difficult, Kapitan.  But I do all my best thinking while moving.
You do everything while running.
Anyway, I wanted to know what is required to start a competition.

Fields.MenuText: I want to help as much as I can.
You should talk to the Navy about that.
Perhaps there is a sporting authority you could talk to?

Fields.DialogueText: Świetny! There must be one nearby! Probably they have all kinds of forms I'll need to fill out...
I do not think they like using funds for this sort of thing, nie? Well, there is a form for everything.
Do you know which forms I need to fill out for this?
It's honestly remarkable to me that you even started looking for forms.
I was not going to, but one of the lejtnants told me it would be useful.
Kapitan, Blyskawica, Morganas are approaching the port!
@BATTLE
Cholera! My notes are all destroyed!
You were very electric this battle. Perhaps you torched them by accident?
Jestem zla! I am going for a run! I must remember everything now!
I have very good balance, Kapitan.
And is that your third bowl of beans in the last hour?
How have you not spilled that already?
Tak, Kapitan.
Well, I hope it gives you the energy to fight. Here they come!
It is funny that you think they are coming to me, rather than the other way around.
@BATTLE
How do you feel after that? You're still glowing a little.
I am hungry.

Fields.MenuText: How are you still hungry after eating that much?
What do you want to eat?
Actually, I'm feeling hungry too now.

Fields.DialogueText: We just had a battle! Everyone is hungry after exercising.
Unless the mess has changed the menu, I will have the beans again.
Then let us eat together!
This is a weird question to ask a ship, but how do you eat that much?
You should run as much as I do. Then tell me if you are hungry!
Point me directly at her! I want to finish this quickly!
@BATTLE
Ahead full, into the wind.
Yes, Captain!
On second thought, flank speed. Blyskawica is already starting to glow.
Sometimes I feel so slow! We could have caught her much faster if I could train my engines like I train these legs!
I love these legs! They are very useful! You like these legs too, Kapitan?

Fields.MenuText: I have elected not to answer that.
Yes, Blyskawica, I love your legs.
I prefer the engines.

Fields.DialogueText: Why not? It is a simple question.
You have good legs too, Kapitan. You should run with me.
But I cannot jump with engines, or do a handstand on them.  Although I cannot do a handstand on legs either.
Actually, Blyskawica, I was wondering how your competition papers were coming.
O! Kapitan, I spoke to the Royal Navy, and they told me it was an excellent idea!
Well, that's--
But they also tell me I must get many more forms! I have to fill out forms for each event! I must get it approved by them!
I must get it approved by the port we have the contests in and fill papers for them!
I must speak with the local sporting people of the city or country and they will help me!  Then I must talk with the news because it must be a public event!
I'm not sure about talking to the news...
Teraz jestem zla. I am going to run.
That looks easy enough. Sixty more meters and you would cross the finish line!
How can anyone cartwheel one hundred meters?
*THUD*
It is easy! First you must raise your hands over your head. Then you launch yourself forward!
You let your momentum carry you over... And, voila, you land on your feet!
I don't think you should do that in a dress.
Appreciation of an athlete is part of enjoying athletics! Is that not right, Kapitan?

Fields.MenuText: Don't ask me. I'm just enjoying the show.
Sure! I'll appreciate athletes.
That was an impressive cartwheel!

Fields.DialogueText: At least you understand the fun of it.
Yes! If you understand, then I am sure the other Corki Juracie will.
Dziekuje, Kapitan, but that is not what I asked.
So how far can you go, Blyskawica?
Perhaps fifteen meters.
So why would you make everyone go one hundred meters?
What is the point of having a body if I cannot push the limits of it?
Morganas have been spotted! We need to sortie!
We should deal with them quickly, then race back so I can show you the other events I want in my competition!
@BATTLE
Tak, I am very excited to talk about my event.  I know it is not quite ready yet, but I cannot wait!
Bottle of whiskey, that's how you say it, right?
Nie, it is--
Bottle of whiskey, what is the biggest Morgana you have ever had to take down?
I thought this was supposed to be about my athletic competition!
Yes, yes. So I've heard that you actually shoot lightning when you fight! Is there a reason for that?
Kapitan, tell them to only ask about my event!

Fields.MenuText: I can't control the press. Nobody can.
Can you do it after you answer their questions?
I'm not saying anything that they can put in the papers.

Fields.DialogueText: The Germans and the Soviets are doing it.
Their questions are not good questions.
I'm going to say some things they cannot put in the papers if they do not stop.
Well, why don't you just be yourself?
I will try.
Bottle of whiskey! Over here! I've heard you're one of the fastest ships in the fleet. Is that true?
I am not just a fast ship! With this body I am faster than any of you running!
I am also very good at jumping. O! I can stand on my hands like this!
Do not put a picture of that in the papers. If any of you wish to race me, you may try.
*WIND*
Actually, I wanted to ask--
If you have any more questions, you must race me on the water.  I sense a Morgana approaching.
May we film the battle for the newsreels?
Nie, you may not. Now, I must run!
I am going to host an athletic competition soon! Many of the Corki Juracie and I will gather to race and jump and have other contests of skill.
I am very excited to host this, and I believe this contest will bring many people together for fun!
@BATTLE
Kapitan, Kapitan! I am excited - the English press want to hear of my event!
That's great news! Do you already know what you're going to tell them?
*ALARM*
@BATTLE
And she's run off again.  Well, she'll be back after the fight.
Kapitan! The English press wish to interview me about my athletic event!
Deja vu.
This is so exciting! I must prepare to talk to them.
I don't think you need to prepare.  You should just--
*FOOTSTEPS*
Is there an emotion she has that doesn't make her run?
Przepraszam! I got so excited I had to run a lap around the deck!
As I was saying, just...

Fields.MenuText: ... don't be too... yourself.
... take a few deep breaths.
... don't run off in the middle of the interview.

Fields.DialogueText: I know it is difficult for me to stand still, but I can handle a few questions.
I can take many quick breaths and do it faster.
What if they ask how fast I am? Should I not run?
Whatever you do, just don't let anything weird end up in a newsreel.
I make no promises, Kapitan.
Whew! Another good fight.
O! Starszy marynarz! What is that you are holding?
Ah! Uh... It is a pin I found in a shop last time we made port. I thought it might bring good luck.
Ja chce tego. Show me where to get one! We will run and get it now!
Hold on, Blyskawica, we just got out of a fight. Why do you want that so bad?
Look! It is shaped like lightning! It is beautiful and powerful. You understand, Kapitan?
Trinkets of lightning are all so similar, yet very different.  No two bolts of lightning are the same, and nor are any two gems or trinkets.
So if I cannot get one now, you must get one for me next time we are in port!

Fields.MenuText: You can't just send me on a shopping trip!
Don't you have paperwork to do for your competition?
Sailor, which port were we at when you found that?

Fields.DialogueText: If I cannot go, you must.
If I finish it by the time we make port, will you buy two?
Dziekuje, Kapitan! We will go there immediately!
Not yet, Blyskawica. We still have to finish this patrol. I heard there is a storm to the east, likely accompanied by Morganas.
I do not know what it is, but I feel particularly lucky today, Kapitan! Attack faster!
@BATTLE
I have a collection of them myself! Many gems and trinkets and things with the shape and style!
O, that should be very fun, Kapitan! Give me a course east!
But you know this does not excuse you from buying me a trinket.
Blyskawica! I've been looking for you everywhere!
Not now, Kapitan, I am getting ready for the fight!
Blyskawica, I see that storm, but we don't know there are Morganas in there!
I'm sure there are, Kapitan. Do you not know to trust a girl's intuition?
I trust by the giant stack of papers you left on my desk that you're trying to avoid bureaucracy.
Look, Kapitan! I see a Morgana out there!
@BATTLE
I still want to know what the stack of papers in my quarters is.
It is just some of the forms for my competition.

Fields.MenuText: But why are they on my desk?
On second thought, the stack doesn't look that big.
That sounds important.  Do you want me to hold on to them?

Fields.DialogueText: I do not have my own quarters, so I used yours.
It is a lot of papers. I do not think you would chase after me for a small stack.
That is not why they are there, Kapitan.
Why don't you just fill them out and get it over with quickly?
It is not that simple, Kapitan!
First I was required to submit a form for each event, which I think is too much.
Then they decided I must have safety forms for each event, along with a number of silly requests.
Some of my events are "too outlandish," they tell me!
What is the point of having a body like this if you do not use it to its best potential?
Blyskawica...
Blyskawica!
Tak, Kapitan?
Come with me. I'll help you sort all of it out.
Now move your feet faster!
This isn't easy to do slowly, Blyskawica.
Then do it faster!  This dance is in triple time.
The way you do it feels more like quintuple time.
It is simple - you move your body like this! Listen to Chopin! He guides your motion.
First you step like this!
Then you step this way, and back quickly! We separate, and I will come back to you while you dance!
What is this dance *huff* called again?
It is the Mazurka. It is so much fun! It reminds me of home!
I would dance it every day there!

Fields.MenuText: Is it your favorite dance?
Do all Polish dances have so much footwork?
Can you practice with someone else?

Fields.DialogueText: I love all my dances equally. I want you to experience them all!
Not all! In some of them you lift your partner and carry them with you.
This is not practice. I am teaching every person I can about our great dances!
At least you're dedicated.
Tak, and you will be too, Kapitan!
Now again from the top! We can do it twice more before we are in range to shoot at the Morganas!
What Morganas?
I have it under control, Kapitan. Focus on your footwork!
@BATTLE
What was that argument about, Blyskawica?
I am getting tired of the food. I want some of our food from home!
Like schabowy! I love schabowy! The pork is so sweet and tender!
I know we probably can't make bigos on the ship, but we can at least make schabowy!
How did this turn into an argument?
I don't have the materials for those! We're in a war, you know.
Kapitan! We must get the ingredients for them! I want to eat more than our usual rations!
If you can say that when you aren't stuffing those rations in your mouth, I would consider it.

Fields.MenuText: All right, I'll consider it next time we make port.
He's right, there is a war on.  We have trouble getting the ingredients we have.
I would like to try these foods too.

Fields.DialogueText: Thank you, Kapitan.  Make sure we have enough for many good meals!
Are you certain we can not spare a even a little for a ship on the front?
You really should, Kapitan! They are much better than the ship's rations.
No matter what we have, the crew can't fight on an empty stomach.
And I cannot run on one. Do you know how difficult it is to run with some of these rations?
I think it's a bad idea to run with food in general.
Perhaps we can test how well they fight on an empty stomach after we beat the Morganas approaching from the north!
... You really should tell me about these things ahead of time.
@BATTLE
You're almost finished, but you've been putting it off for too long.
I just do not see why we must do so much to be allowed to run.
It's more than just running.
I know! That is why I am so excited! It is also the long jump, and the twenty-yard handstand, and the--
Blyskawica, focus.
O, tak. Well hand me the papers and I shall finish signing them. That is the last part, yes?

Fields.MenuText: Yes, it looks like the last one.
No, there are plenty more hidden in my pockets.
Don't worry, I'll take care of it if there is more.

Fields.DialogueText: Wreszcie! I was drowning in this.
If that is true I will electrocute you.
Dziekuje, Kapitan. I will be very grateful.
Once this is all done, we can finally hold your competition!
Can this last page wait for later?
No, why?
Because there is a Morgana! I will race you to the bridge!
One of these days she'll sign that last page.
@BATTLE
Kapitan! Kapitan! Do you like my ribbons?
You got new ones?
*ALARM*
Run me straight at them, Kapitan! I think I feel a storm coming!
@BATTLE
Is it just me or did you produce more lightning in that fight?
I was just excited, Kapitan! Grom keeps finding such good ribbons, and these are no exception!
Which one do you like best, Kapitan? The blue? The yellow? The one with flowers?

Fields.MenuText: I like the light blue ribbon.
I like the yellow one.
I like the one with flowers.

Fields.DialogueText: Dziekuje, Kapitan, it reminds me of the lightning!
Dziekuje, Kapitan. It makes me feel faster somehow!
Dziekuje, Kapitan. It reminds me of my sister and my home.
I think they're all pretty on you.
O, Kapitan, do you want to see them flow behind me? They will look much better when I am running!
Perhaps they will look better when I jump!
Kapitan, I have a solution! We shall test both.
Tak, Kapitan! I did not think my other ribbons were well suited to the competition.
And these ones will be?
That is why I am showing them to you, Kapitan. I must look my best in my own contest!
*Huff* Kapitan? Do you need something?
No I... Are you out of breath?
Tak, Kapitan. I am feeling tired.
I'm almost afraid to ask how it's even possible for you.
I have spent the last fifteen hours running. This is my *huff* first break.
I believe you, but now I am wondering why.
I am training for my competition, of course! How could you forget?
O! Kapitan, I have an idea! You should race me around the deck! The first back here wins!

Fields.MenuText: I don't think that's a good idea.
Sure, but I don't think I'll win.
You're on! You look tired enough that I have a chance!

Fields.DialogueText: It is a great idea! Come catch me!
Nonsense! If you practice enough, you may even become faster than me!
Now that you have said that, I cannot lose!
Wait, Blyskawica! That's the--
O! Kapitan! You are already here! You cannot go through bulkheads, so how did you get back so fast?
Unless you did not start? No matter, there are Morganas approaching.
Do biegu...
*ALARM*
Gotowi...
Do not worry! If anything, I can fight even better after exercise like this!
@BATTLE
... General quarters alarm.
This is quite the gathering you've made.
Tak, Kapitan! We are doing the Krakowiak.

Fields.MenuText: That's another one of your dances, right?
The crack of a whip?
I think I've heard of that one.

Fields.DialogueText: Tak, Kapitan! That is precisely what it is!
Nie, Kapitan, the Krakowiak. It is one of my favorite dances!
Tak, Kapitan! It is one of the best dances from Poland!
The Polish sailors gathered because they were getting homesick, so I suggested we dance!
To recognize a true Pole, make them dance a Krakowiak!
O! Kapitan, a Morgana wants to ruin our fun. I will make her regret that very quickly.
@BATTLE
As I was saying, Kapitan, the Krakowiak has many different versions from all over Poland!
I'm just glad you don't expect me to have it memorized.
We will get to that. First you must join us this time!
Everyone must partner up. Traditionally the lead pair does most of the singing.
Oh, good, so--
And Kapitan, since you are my partner, I will do the singing!
NOW START THE MUSIC! I WISH TO DANCE!
Now hold on, Blyskawica, what about training for your competition?
I am training! I am perhaps worried that as one of very few Polish Corki Juracie, we will make a poor showing.
So I must get both the crew and myself in the mood, and what better way than athletic tradition, nie?
I get to use my legs, and to use my heart. This, too, is training!
Blyskawica?  What are you doing up there?
I am practicing!
*CLANG*
I almost had it that time!
Let me guess, the long jump?
Nie, Kapitan! The high jump! If I can make it from the top of A turret all the way over B turret, I should have a chance!
*BOOM*
*SPLASH*
Blyskawica! I think we're under attack!
Do not worry, Kapitan, I will get it!
@BATTLE
What were you doing back there? You were hardly in this fight at all!
I almost made the jump after that third salvo, Kapitan! Or was it the fourth?

Fields.MenuText: You need to focus on our surroundings more!
You need to pick a better time to practice.
I saw! That was an amazing jump.

Fields.DialogueText: I can do both, Kapitan!
I think that was a great time to practice.
Not good enough! I need to practice more.
Don't worry, Blyskawica. When the time comes, I'm certain you'll be the best.
The only way to be the best is to train more than everyone else.
... An eating contest?
Some of the men thought they had a chance. I tried to warn them how many times she comes in here each day.
Well, it had better start soon. I don't think she's sat down for this long in a while.
I think you're right, Captain. She looks about ready to flip that table.
@BATTLE
Congratulations on your victory, Blyskawica.
That is weird. I think I have more energy than usual.
Kapitan, your hair is standing straight up. You should get that checked. I do not think it is heatlhy.
I'm going to use this extra energy to train. Maybe it will give me the edge I need to win in my contest.

Fields.MenuText: How many laps are you planning to do?
Perhaps if you don't, you won't need to eat for a while?
I've heard exercise after eating can give you cramps.

Fields.DialogueText: As many as I can, Kapitan.
I do not think it works that way.
Really? It has never happened to me, and I eat while running.
While you run, it looks like we have a few sailors to take to the doc.
From the battle or the subsequent eating competition?
*ALARM*
*BOOM*
See? I told you she would flip it.  And the eating contest hasn't even started.
I'm not surprised. You just ate more than thirty cans of beans.
Both.
The wounded from the battle should be treated. The sailors incapacitated by food should race me until they work off the energy!
It's nothing wrong with me.
Kapitan! You are just in time to join us!
Ah, so this is why I was hearing Chopin from my quarters.
Can you believe the competition is tomorrow? I cannot wait!
Yes, I can see. You've almost thrown that poor sailor.
*THUD*
O! I did not realize I was dancing so quickly. Kapitan! Do you want to be my dancing partner?

Fields.MenuText: Of course, Blyskawica.
No, I have captain business to attend to.
Do you plan to throw me?

Fields.DialogueText: I think I am too excited. You should lead, Kapitan.
That is a quick way to ruin the mood. Come dance with me!
I do not intend to throw you, but I will if it is required to make you dance with me.
All right, you've convinced me. Take my hand, Blyskawica.
Of course, Kapitan! The faster we dance, the faster we can sink the Morganas coming to ruin the celebration!
Remember what I said about telling me ahead of time?
Do not fuss and enjoy the music, Kapitan!
@BATTLE
So you're really that worked up about the competition, Blyskawica?
Should I not be? My arms and legs are more excited than my heart.
My head is not at all concerned.  Is that weird, Kapitan? I do not think it is weird.
Blyskawica, I can't keep up if you speed up the dance like this!
It is tomorrow! Imagine if I do not do well! Nie, I must warm up all night or my muscles will not be ready for the contest!
I don't think that's--
Thank you for the advice, Kapitan! Dancing with you always helps me to think!
I didn't--
You stay here, I will go practice! Sleep well so you can cheer for me with your entire voice!
This is our last fight before the competition, Kapitan!
I'm ready if you are!
@BATTLE
Get ready to watch me, Kapitan! I'm going to win the long jump for sure!
You've already won half the other events, Blyskawica. Leave a medal or two for anybody else.
Do not even joke like that, Kapitan. If they wanted to win, they would have trained their bodies harder than me.
And who was late writing out all of the invitations?
... Look, Kapitan! The race is starting! I must run!

Fields.MenuText: Good luck!
Break a leg!
Didn't you say long jump?

Fields.DialogueText: Dziekuje, Kapitan!
That sounds like bad luck to say before a race.
No, I am certain I said race.
Don't forget to cheer for me, Kapitan!
